   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> They changed Njords Fury, the low end style with high damage and a med-duration stun to chain off of Frost Cut. Frost Cut is a lvl 4 style off of a block. <br>
<br>
Advantages to using shield:<br>
<br>
5%+ block rate depending on dex.<br>
Extra stats from the shield. <br>
Possibly awesome style combo.<br>
More proc damage<br>
<br>
Disadvantages:<br>
<br>
Gives up 15% 2-handed damage bonus.<br>
Slightly lower parry rate because of the order in which block/parry are checked.<br>
<br>
<br>
Thoughts? It looks like I'm going to be doing some testing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A> at: 6/19/02 8:13:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/unamuna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namuna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 1:17:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> From what Sanya has stated, the resolution of attack order has chance-to-parry FIRST, before chance-to-block...So using a shield has no bearing on Parry rate because the checks are done to Parry first.<br>
<br>
But other disadvantages;<br>
<br>
- My perception of my Skald is Light Tank/Light Armory. Making Njord's Fury chain off a block style caters to the Main Tanks.<br>
- I've got to spend valuable Realm Skill pts on Blocking to even make it decent. Until further tests/results come out that prove that Frost/Njord kicks ass...The price of it isn't worth it.<br>
- The 39 spec styles for Axes and Hammers can be achieved by a 2Hand user (Axes=Beside, Hammers=Parry), but the change to Sword will be usable by 1H/Shield users ONLY<br>
<br>
My templat to 50 is probably going to be 46Song/44Weapon or 47Weapon...I'm ALL ABOUT up-front dmg, that means 2Handed Sword, so this change basically SUCKS for me.<br>
<br>
I wait ANXIOUSLY for the respec. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 1:24:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> Well yes and no. <br>
<br>
If you want to be able to get it in (given we can't spec in shields) you'll really need to put realm skill points into the mastery of blocking skill (aug dex pre-req). With enough levels of that you should get your blocks in.<br>
<br>
However what I will be doing is not worrying about it for RvR, but keeping it available for occasions when I have to play primary tank, and switch to my sword/shield set up and quick bar. In these occasions it'll help but it's not really anything to write home about.<br>
<br>
It is a lot better news for my high shield spec Warrior however as he also uses sword. So maybe he won't re-spec to hammer after all. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/unamuna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namuna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 2:29:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> Here's another wacky thought...Do blocks from fellow groupmates (if you're in a group) count towards the prereq?<br>
<br>
As I recall, it DOES. So in actuality this could be okay, IF we're grouped with a Warrior or Thane.<br>
<br>
*shrug* we'll see. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dane>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 10:30:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> I agree, looks nice.<br>
<br>
Styles can really change a battle.  High damage alone on a chain style is huge..with a med. stun that's devastating.  1H and shield is definitely viable...and with this nice combo, it's even more attractive.<br>
<br>
Correcton:<br>
  I have read a Mythic post that faster weapons do not proc more than a slower weapon.  It's buried in the dev posts.  I got all worried about infiltrators with fast thrust procs and had to find out if they really had an advantage.  Unless, of course, they didn't implement it right and you've tested that it's not working.<br>
<br>
Other disadvantages:<br>
  1H is easier for an opponent to parry.<br>
  1H has a smaller 0 delay damage bonus<br>
<br>
-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 1:46:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> Fast weapons proc more over time, in my experience. I believe that all weapons proc at the same rate (10%). That means if you swing twice as fast you will get twice as many procs. Since proc damage isn't scaled with weapon speed, thats more damage. <br>
<br>
If you really really really insist, I can do testing.<br>
<br>
<br>
Maybe parry is before block. I'll have to look into that when I feel motivated.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 4:40:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> Gis, I insist. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Testing is good (and I'm grumpy cause I missed the copy boat <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Nam, some styles are off you blocking/parrying some are off anyone doing it. IIRC<br>
<br>
Sword off block style is only if *you* block, but the off parry style is if *anyone* parries.<br>
<br>
Axe and Hammer is the other way around. I think this is to make the later reactionary style more useful (off parry comes later for sword and off block comes later for axe and hammer). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 8:39:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> Hmm. I'll see what I can do about the procing. Maybe buy some emerald seal weapons to test with.<br>
<br>
&quot;Q: I gotta say I totally disagree with the order of resolution you posted awhile back because of (insert extremely long log file here). <br>
<br>
A: One email is a lone crackpot, two emails is a possible problem – and I got more than two emails on the subject. So I went and poked someone with a stick, and got the following answer – the order is evade, parry, shield, guard, hit/miss, and lastly bladeturn (if hit = yes). Try THAT and see if it’s correct. &quot;<br>
<br>
So I was wrong :P.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvivaxkithicor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vivax Kithicor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/22/02 5:19:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sword users...worth using shield/1-hander now?</span><hr size=1> On keep doors, I use 1h Sword (Legion) and shield (dragon).  Those extra arrow blocks make a lot of difference.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, if noone's shooting at me, I use my 2h sword.  (K-Mart)<br>
<br>
Respec to hammer?  I'll have to consider it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=200.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=200.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=200.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=200.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=200.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=200.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="teamskaldfrm1">General Discussion<option value="teamskaldfrm6">Bug Forum - General<option value="teamskaldfrm4">Logs and Test Results<option value="teamskaldfrm7">Wish List<option value="teamskaldfrm9">Equipment Discussions<option value="teamskaldfrm10">RvR Discussions<option